theorem Topology.closureInterior_subset_closureInterior_union
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) ⊆
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- First, prove the inclusion for the interiors themselves.
  have h_subset : (interior (A ∪ B) : Set X) ⊆
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
    intro x hx
    -- `interior (A ∪ B)` splits as the union of the two interiors.
    have hx' : x ∈ interior A ∪ interior B := by
      simpa [interior_union] using hx
    cases hx' with
    | inl hA =>
        exact Or.inl (subset_closure hA)
    | inr hB =>
        exact Or.inr (subset_closure hB)
  -- The right-hand side is a closed set.
  have h_closed : IsClosed (closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B)) := by
    have h_closedA : IsClosed (closure (interior A)) := isClosed_closure
    have h_closedB : IsClosed (closure (interior B)) := isClosed_closure
    exact h_closedA.union h_closedB
  -- Conclude using the minimality of the closure.
  exact closure_minimal h_subset h_closed

theorem Topology.Subset_closureInterior_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ B) (hB : Topology.P1 B) :
    (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hB
  exact Set.Subset.trans hAB hB
